        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-02T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-02T20:00:00-05:00" n="1056" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1056">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860h.01/12–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-02T20:00:00-05:00">January 2, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Urtel 796, Dec 26. We do not feel that publication instruction in Yugos press
                    should be made condition to presentation new letters of credence. Text is being
                    fully reported in Yugos broadcasts from radio this country and to increase
                    circulation in Yugos we think you might properly have copies available at
                    Embassy for distribution to interested callers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
